    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="674"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.R27/65.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">King of England</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <placeName type="venue">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Buckingham Palace</hi>
                            </placeName>, <lb/>
                            <placeName type="city">
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                            </placeName>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is with the deepest sorrow that I have to inform you of the death of Mr.
                    Whitelaw Reid, at noon to-day. As your Ambassador in this country his loss will
                    be sincerely deplored, while personally I shall mourn for an old friend of many
                    years standing for whom I had the greatest regard and respect. The Queen and I
                    sympathize most warmly with Mrs. Whitelaw Reid in her heavy sorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George, R. I</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
